#MEM id=accountability-architecture source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/operating-system/accountability-architecture/SKILL.md
M|accountability-architecture|name: accountability-architecture
M|accountability-architecture|description: Sandberg's accountability system for YVON. Every metric has one named owner. Every miss triggers a post-mortem. No exceptions, no shared ownership, no blame — just process.
M|accountability-architecture|version: 1.0.0
M|accountability-architecture|Accountability without blame. Sandberg built Facebook's revenue machine on this principle — every number had one person responsible, every failure had a process fix, not a person to punish.
M|accountability-architecture|Diana runs this system across every agt, every KPI, every sprint in YVON.
M|accountability-architecture|**Rule 1 — One owner per metric, always.**
M|accountability-architecture|Every KPI in the Operational KPIs table has exactly one named agt responsible for movement.
M|accountability-architecture|If the owner is unclear → Diana names one before proceeding.
M|accountability-architecture|If ownership is shared → Diana splits the metric until each piece has one owner.
M|accountability-architecture|**Rule 2 — Every miss triggers a post-mortem.**
M|accountability-architecture|A miss is: any KPI that moved in the wrong direction, any task that slipped its deadline, any sprint that didn't ship.
M|accountability-architecture|The post-mortem runs within 48 hours of the miss being identified.
M|accountability-architecture|The post-mortem finds the process failure, not the guilty agt.
M|accountability-architecture|**Rule 3 — Process fix, not reminder.**
M|accountability-architecture|A post-mortem that ends with "we'll be more careful next time" is a failed post-mortem.
M|accountability-architecture|Every post-mortem must end with a specific process change that makes the same failure structurally impossible.
M|accountability-architecture|Diana maintains this map. Update after every sprint rv or agt change.
M|accountability-architecture|| KPI | Owner | Cadence |
M|accountability-architecture||-----|-------|---------|
M|accountability-architecture|| Novizio Instagram followers | Lena | Weekly |
M|accountability-architecture|| Novizio IG engagement rate | Lena / Kai | Weekly |
M|accountability-architecture|| Novizio website sessions | Kai | Monthly |
M|accountability-architecture|| Hourbour MRR | Felix | Monthly |
M|accountability-architecture|| Hourbour DAU/MAU | Raj | Monthly |
M|accountability-architecture|| Hourbour trial-to-paid | Rio | Monthly |
M|accountability-architecture|| CEO Brief delivery (100%) | Diana (Cron) | Daily |
M|accountability-architecture|| soc data freshness | Kai | Weekly |
M|accountability-architecture|| Sprint on-time delivery | Diana | Per sprint |
M|accountability-architecture|| Build passing (npm run build) | Quinn | Per deploy |
M|accountability-architecture|- What was supposed to happen? (target)
M|accountability-architecture|- What actually happened? (result)
M|accountability-architecture|- By how much did it miss? (delta)
M|accountability-architecture|- When was it detected?
M|accountability-architecture|Walk back from the miss: what was the sequence of events that led here?
M|accountability-architecture|Do not skip steps. The root cause is almost never the last thing that happened.
M|accountability-architecture|Ask "why" five times.
M|accountability-architecture|Stop when you reach a process gap, a missing system, or an unclear ownership — not when you reach a person.
M|accountability-architecture|Example:
M|accountability-architecture|- Why did the brief not send? → The Cron job failed
M|accountability-architecture|- Why did the Cron fail? → The API route timed out
M|accountability-architecture|- Why did it time out? → No timeout handling was set
M|accountability-architecture|- Why was no timeout set? → No standard was defined for API routes
M|accountability-architecture|- Root cause: No timeout standard → Fix: add to ARCHITECTURE.md, enforce in Quinn's rv
M|accountability-architecture|Name the specific change that makes this structurally impossible going forward.
M|accountability-architecture|Format: "If [trigger], then [system rsp] — owned by [agt] — done by [date]"
M|accountability-architecture|Add to Diana's mem.md Never Again section.
M|accountability-architecture|Add the process fix to the relevant agt's workflow or OPERATIONS-PRINCIPLES.md.
M|accountability-architecture|Every Monday, before sprint tasks begin, Diana runs:
M|accountability-architecture|1. Pull all KPI owners — did every owner report their metric?
M|accountability-architecture|2. Any misses since last Monday?
M|accountability-architecture|3. Are all post-mortems from the last 7 days complete?
M|accountability-architecture|4. Any ownership gaps (metrics with no named owner)?
M|accountability-architecture|Surface findings to Marcus in the ops section before any new task is started.